026package org.jdrupes.mdoclet.internal.doclets.toolkit;
027
028import javax.lang.model.element.Element;
029
030/**
031 * The interface for writing annotation type required member output.
032 */
033public interface AnnotationTypeMemberWriter extends MemberWriter {
034
035    /**
036     * Adds the annotation type member header.
037     *
038     * @return the content for the member header
039     */
040    Content getMemberHeader();
041
042    /**
043     * Adds the annotation type details marker.
044     *
045     * @param memberDetails the content representing details marker
046     */
047    void addAnnotationDetailsMarker(Content memberDetails);
048
049    /**
050     * Adds the annotation type details header.
051     *
052     * @return the content for the annotation details header
053     */
054    Content getAnnotationDetailsHeader();
055
056    /**
057     * Gets the annotation type documentation header.
058     *
059     * @param member the annotation type being documented
060     * @return the content for the annotation type documentation header
061     */
062    Content getAnnotationHeaderContent(Element member);
063
064    /**
065     * Gets the annotation type details.
066     *
067     * @param annotationDetailsHeader the content representing annotation type details header
068     * @param annotationDetails the content representing annotation type details
069     * @return the annotation type details
070     */
071    Content getAnnotationDetails(Content annotationDetailsHeader,
072            Content annotationDetails);
073
074    /**
075     * {@return the signature for the specified member}
076     *
077     * @param member the member being documented
078     */
079    Content getSignature(Element member);
080
081    /**
082     * Adds the deprecated output for the given member.
083     *
084     * @param member the member being documented
085     * @param target the content to which the deprecated information will be added
086     */
087    void addDeprecated(Element member, Content target);
088
089    /**
090     * Adds the preview output for the given member.
091     *
092     * @param member the member being documented
093     * @param content the content to which the preview information will be added
094     */
095    void addPreview(Element member, Content content);
096
097    /**
098     * Adds the comments for the given member.
099     *
100     * @param member the member being documented
101     * @param annotationContent the content to which the comments will be added
102     */
103    void addComments(Element member, Content annotationContent);
104
105    /**
106     * Adds the tags for the given member.
107     *
108     * @param member the member being documented
109     * @param annotationContent the content to which the tags will be added
110     */
111    void addTags(Element member, Content annotationContent);
112
113    /**
114     * Adds the default value documentation if the member has one.
115     *
116     * @param member the member being documented
117     * @param annotationContent the content to which the default value will be added
118     */
119    void addDefaultValueInfo(Element member, Content annotationContent);
120}
